THE CONVENTIONS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  A (Standard Weyl):  (2/5, 2/3, 2/3) per Weyl fermion
  B (Standard Dirac): (4/5, 4/3, 4/3) = 2*A, per Dirac
  C (Library Dynkin):  (2/5, 2/3, 1/3) per VL pair

  A is for chiral SM fermions (Weyl).
  B is for the VL pair (one Dirac = L + R).
  C is what the library uses for the VL pair.

