    Component 3: library = 1/3, Weyl = 2/3
  Library matches Dirac: False
    Component 1: library = 1/15, Dirac = 2/15
    Component 2: library = 1, Dirac = 2
    Component 3: library = 1/3, Dirac = 4/3

THE DIVERGENCE: SU(3) COEFFICIENT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Standard Weyl:  Db_3 = (2/3) * T(R_3) * dim(R_2)
  Library Dynkin:  Db_3 = (1/3) * dim(R_2) * S_2(R_3)
  Coefficient ratio: 1/3 vs 2/3 = factor of 2.

  For b_1 and b_2 the library matches Weyl exactly.
  The divergence is ONLY in the SU(3) coefficient.

  Applied to SM fermions:
    Conv A: b_3 fermion per gen = 4/3, total = 4
    Conv C: b_3 fermion per gen = 2/3, total = 2
    Correct value: 4 (gives b_3_SM = -7)
    Conv C gives: 2 (gives b_3_SM = -9)

