  MSSM                                  7/5          1.4      0.04181

  Measured gap ratio (dimensionless)       1.3581926841

WHAT IS THE VL PAIR?
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  A vector-like pair (3,2,1/6) consists of:
    L component: one Weyl in (3,2,1/6)
    R component: one Weyl in (3*,2*,-1/6)
  Together = one Dirac fermion.

  SM chiral fermions are summed as Weyl (Conv A).
  The VL pair should use the Dirac formula (Conv B = 2*A).

  The library uses Conv C which has a non-standard
  SU(3) coefficient. This is neither Weyl nor Dirac.

THE SESSION 3 QUESTION
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  The library's SM betas (41/10, -19/6, -7) are correct
  and standard. They were NOT computed from Convention C —
  they are hardcoded from the literature.

  The VL shifts (1/15, 1, 1/3) were computed from the
  library's Dynkin formulas (Convention C). The gap ratio
  38/27 combines correct SM betas with Convention C shifts.

  If the VL shifts should be (2/15, 2, 4/3) (Dirac),
  the gap ratio becomes 6/5 = 1.2, not 38/27.

  The Session 3 checks verified internal consistency
  (the arithmetic is correct given the library values),
  not that the library values are physically correct.

RESOLUTION PATH
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  An external reference must settle whether the VL
  (3,2,1/6) one-loop shift for SU(3) is 1/3 or 4/3.

  Candidates:
    Kowalska & Kumar, JHEP 12 (2019) 094
    Bhattacherjee et al., JHEP 05 (2018) 090
    Dermisek, Phys. Rev. D 87 (2013) 055008

  Until resolved, both gap ratios must be tracked:
    38/27 = 1.407 (library, Db_3=1/3)
    6/5 = 1.2 (Dirac, Db_3=4/3)

